<h2 class="bac"><img class="pclose" src="../images/clear.gif">Our Business</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">To deliver a best in class Internship opportunity for Operations MAP (OMAP) participants through experiential learning, training, and networking opportunities.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Overview</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">The Operations MAP (OMAP) Internship is a 10 week summer program designed to provide external candidates and selected internal associates with an opportunity for leadership positions in the bank&#39;s operational lines of business. OMAP Interns participate in a variety of activities designed to foster teamwork, encourage networking, and demonstrate Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America&#39;s vision and culture. Interns are given a true associate experience, including goal-setting and a formal review process.</p>
<p class="bac nobr">10 week Summer Internship roles and responsibilities may include:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Business Support Lead: Provides business support to a team; responsibilities include data collection and analysis, project implementation/point of contact, and performance catalyst.</li>
	<li>Operations Team Lead: Directs a small unit or section of internal operations activities; responsibilities focus on the day to day resolution of problems and execution of transactions within specific operations units requiring immediate and frequent involvement with unit activities.</li>
	<li>Operations Analyst: Performs day-to-day analysis, research and resolution of varied problems; administers defined procedures, analysis/report generation, and exception processing.</li>
	<li>Change Analyst: Acts as a supporting role on change initiatives via the facilitation of project workgroup meetings, management of project documentation standards and system/s of record, and the delivery of implementation and control plans.</li>
	<li>Process Design Analyst: Supports the Process Design Consultant with the integration of best practices to ensure continuous process improvement; analyzes, updates and implements procedures utilizing process improvement models and techniques.</li>
	<li>Operational Risk Specialist: Analyzes existing practices within operational risk management across the company in the areas of data management, data quality, information and reporting; develops solutions to problems identified which yield productivity gains consistent with company goals.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Qualifications</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">We hire an elite group of new associates with a minimum 3.0 grade point average. Successful candidates will possess and demonstrate the ability to work in a fast paced, empowered environment. Ideal candidates will have the demonstrated ability to handle multiple, competing priorities; learn new tools/applications quickly; and possess strong interpersonal skills.</p>
<p class="bac">Ideal candidates will demonstrate the ability to lead and manage people (indirect  &amp; direct), inspect and understand a business end to end (process  &amp; risks), influence change adoption, lead quality focus (six sigma), communicate effectively, meet challenging performance requirements, learn from past experiences, and use superb analytical and presentation skills to achieve outstanding results.</p>
<p class="bac nobr">Candidate Profile includes:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Working towards a bachelor&#39;s degree in one of the following majors: Business Management, Business Administration, Supply Chain Management, Operations Management, Information Management, Statistics, Economics, or Industrial Engineering</li>
	<li>Demonstration of leadership outside the classroom</li>
	<li>100% geographic flexibility</li>
	<li>Willingness to work varied schedules, including swing shift for specific operations positions</li>
	<li>Solid organizational skills, excellent planning ability, and project management skills</li>
	<li>Ability to communicate effectively in both written and verbal communications</li>
	<li>Sound judgment and the ability to deal with ambiguity and high pressure situations in a changing environment</li>
	<li> High standard of professionalism</li>
	<li>Unlimited authorization to work in the United States</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Training</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac nobr">The program consists of the following developmental activities and opportunities:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>On-boarding; including orientation and ongoing structured learning events</li>
	<li>Business critical assignments</li>
	<li>Peer coach support</li>
	<li>Exposure to senior leadership teams through networking events</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

